      • NSDate

        public NSDate(java.lang.String textRepresentation)
       throws java.text.ParseException
        Parses a date from its textual representation. That representation has the following pattern: yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss'Z'
        Parameters:
        textRepresentation - The textual representation of the date (ISO 8601 format)
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException - When the date could not be parsed, i.e. it does not match the expected pattern.
